[[Orochimaru]] gathers "wicked" [[chakra]] to his five fingertips, which he forcefully applies over another seal. When this Five Elements Seal, being of an odd number, is applied over the [[Four Symbols Seal]], being of an even number, the Four Symbols Seal is disrupted because of the odd—even imbalance. In [[Naruto Uzumaki]]'s case, he loses access to the chakra of the [[Nine-Tails]] - which the Four Symbols Seal keeps stored in his body - and furthermore makes it difficult for him to use his own.<ref name="d1"/> When the Five Elements Seal is initially applied, Naruto is rendered unconscious.<ref>''Naruto'' chapter 49</ref> When [[Jiraiya]] is later shown [[Five Elements Unseal|removing]] the Five Elements Seal from Naruto, he is able to correctly guess that Orochimaru applied it in the first place, describing its use as "coarse".<ref>''Naruto'' chapter 91</ref>

== Trivia ==
* The "Five Elements" referred to in the name of this technique are the Chinese Five Elements, the {{translation|''Five Movements''|五行|Japanese: Gogyō, Chinese: Wǔxíng}}:
:# {{translation|Metal|金| ''Chinese:'' jīn}}
:# {{translation|Wood|木| ''Chinese:'' mù}}
:# {{translation|Water|水| ''Chinese:'' shuǐ}}
:# {{translation|Fire|火| ''Chinese:'' huǒ}}
:# {{translation|Earth|土| ''Chinese:'' tǔ}}
